The paper deals with cross-platform video recommendation, which involves information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG) techniques. The proposed model is a deep learning architecture that involves multi-modal autoencoders, which are commonly used in multimedia (MM) and computer vision (CV) applications. Additionally, the model utilizes nonlinear mapping functions, which are also used in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL) applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR and cs.LG, followed by cs.MM, cs.CV, and cs.CL.
